title: Broken Arrow rallies from late deficit to stun Jenks
text:
Posted: 11:31 p.m. Friday, Oct. 23, 2015 Broken Arrow rallies from late deficit to stun Jenks ﻿ PHOTO: Broken Arrow edges past Jenks Sponsored Links By Barry Lewis. Tulsa World JENKS, Okla. — 
Broken Arrow took some unlikely routes Friday night to its biggest football victory since its journey to the 2011 state title game. 
Despite picking up only one first down in the second half, the third-ranked Tigers rallied from being down 13 points late in the third quarter to stun top-ranked Jenks 35-34 at Hunter-Dwelley Stadium. 
It was the first home loss for Jenks since dropping a triple-overtime decision to Booker T. Washington in 2006. 
The victory gives Broken Arrow (7-1, 5-0) sole possession of the District 6AI-1 lead over Jenks (6-1, 4-1), which is looking for a fourth consecutive state title, with two games remaining.
